  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel the<strong> potatoes</strong> and chop them into quarters</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617713443208-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617713443208-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617713443208-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617713443208-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617713443208-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel, core and roughly chop the <strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped apple </strong>to a separate pot with a lid with 75ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [125ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, over a medium-low heat for 15 min or until the apple has softened, stirring occasionally</p><p>Once softened, add a knob of<strong> butter</strong> and mash until smooth, then set aside – this is your <strong>apple sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617713449724-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617713449724-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617713449724-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617713449724-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617713449724-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and slice the <strong>carrots</strong> finely on a diagonal</p><p>Chop the<strong> parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> and <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>herby crumb</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617713476284-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617713476284-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
